The Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC) has disclosed that it is reviewing the National Numbering Plan (NNP) in the spirit of ensuring that the telecom ecosystem is regulated in tandem with the demand of the fourth industrial revolution era. The Executive Vice Chairman of the Commission, Professor Umar Garba Danbatta disclosed this yesterday at the fourth edition of the Information Communication Technology and Telecommunications (ICTEL) exhibition of the Lagos Chamber of Commerce and Industry (LCCI). According to him, the Commission is reviewing the numbering plan with the objective of developing a new one that is robust, futuristic and adaptable to address the numbering needs of the country taking into account the country’s growing population. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE Danbatta who was represented by the Commission’s Deputy Director, Consumer Affairs, Alhaji Ismail Adedigba, said numbering plan is very key to telecommunications services for proper identification of devices and key services. NCC withdraws 36.6m telephone lines from telcos ITU to build cyber security centre in Nigeria NCC to deploy broadband infrastructure to rural areas Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin